## This PR

- clarifies header processing by clients;
- no obligations for servers

## Explicit that

- the exposed `RateLimit-*` values are the ones used to compute the remaining value for the current request;
- they don't provide any obbligation for the server to serve the `Remaining` value.

 - [x]  `Reset` support for sliding window;
   *  see https://github.com/ioggstream/draft-polli-ratelimit-headers/blame/master/draft-polli-ratelimit-headers.md#L179
   * https://github.com/ioggstream/draft-polli-ratelimit-headers/blame/master/draft-polli-ratelimit-headers.md#L214

 - [x]  how to populate `Remaining` & `Reset` when multiple windows apply;

  * https://github.com/ioggstream/draft-polli-ratelimit-headers/blame/master/draft-polli-ratelimit-headers.md#L448
  * https://github.com/ioggstream/draft-polli-ratelimit-headers/blame/master/draft-polli-ratelimit-headers.md#L512

 - [x]  sub-second `Reset`: unsupported 
  
    * https://github.com/ioggstream/draft-polli-ratelimit-headers/blame/master/draft-polli-ratelimit-headers.md#L92

@alranel
